The <b>Sepia-capped Flycatcher</b> (<i>Leptopogon amaurocephalus</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tyrannidae" title="Tyrannidae" class="mw-redirect">Tyrannidae</a> family.
It is found in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentina" title="Argentina">Argentina</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belize" title="Belize">Belize</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia" title="Bolivia">Bolivia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombia" title="Colombia">Colombia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costa_Rica" title="Costa Rica">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecuador" title="Ecuador">Ecuador</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Guiana" title="French Guiana">French Guiana</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala" title="Guatemala">Guatemala</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guyana" title="Guyana">Guyana</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honduras" title="Honduras">Honduras</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicaragua" title="Nicaragua">Nicaragua</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panama" title="Panama">Panama</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paraguay" title="Paraguay">Paraguay</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peru" title="Peru">Peru</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suriname" title="Suriname">Suriname</a>, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Venezuela" title="Venezuela">Venezuela</a>. Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical moist lowland <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a> and heavily degraded former forest.
